<br>
NBG is used when agreed upon 'beforehand' and is oftentimes just plain common courtesy.  And it looks like you have a totally scewed view of what it's supposed to represent.  In your Warrior/Necro example you say the necro should get the SCH:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...He could have sold them and actully bought some half decent gear which would improve his current status dramatically while the warrior would have only see a minor improvement<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's silly.  The warrior is workin as hard for his gear as the next guy.   Most people are honest enough that if they know an item is not an upgrade, they all roll to sell.  If it's an upgrade, and they can wear it, they get it.  Period.  I suppose in your scenario the Necro should get it, then trade it to the Warrior for 2500pp on the spot.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> That's greed, not need</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also Lets say someone said &quot;Hey dude we could really use a chanter for OS&quot; And I already had everything I needed from that zone, gear wize... WHY in the world would i want to go there, when I could get more Xp in Velks or some other zone in which i actully needed gear. Why would anyone chose to go to a zone that offered less XP and no loot over a zone with better XP<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I guess the above quote has some merit, if you are a really selfish dick.  Sorry, I mean <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> needy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> person.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> (This is only the case in random pickup groups, I firmly believe in nb4g during guild/friend groups and guild raids, because they hand down there gear and will eventually help you when you need it)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ahhh, so yer buddies its ok to change yer toon, but the rest of the server can toss off?<br>
