<br>
So in that case yeah, the warrior should get them if he's the only that can use them.  If that warrior has a lot of honor...well that warrior would pass down his current peice to the group, whether they could use it or not, however that doesn't really have to happen to be nbg, it's just a really nice idea.  <br>
<br>
What if something no one can use drops?  Well, by my logic that could sell and bring the same amount of money to anyone in the group, it should be rolled on by all.  Now if you have better gear than most of the group, maybe when it's your time to pick an item you pass.. But you dont have to, you earned that gear just as much as anyone else.<br>
<br>
Exception to this, for me, is in a group of friends or a guild group, something *nice* that none of us can use drops, i have no problem with one of us just keeping it and giving it to a friend/guildie that can use it later.<br>
<br>
Example of greed before need:  Say you were in plane of growth, and there were two clerics.  One cleric had thurgadin legs, one cleric had junky legs.  PoG legs drop, go to the cleric with thurg legs (they are almost the same) because they like them better.  But that cleric doesn't pass down their thurg legs.  That's greedy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dvara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/30/02 6:00:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1477.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_money.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: nbg</span><hr size=1> Look at it another way,<br>
