 I agree with the original intent of the poster. NBFG does not seem to work very well in pickup groups, although it seems to work ok in groups of friends and guildies.  <br>
 Looting on this server is sort of strange.  On mith marr it was almost always master loot, with random on rear items, or alpha loot with a random on rare items.  The alpha looter would loot until they got a certian amount of loot, and then pass it on.  for example most people would alpha loot for 5 plat or a fine steel drop at the gnoll spires in SK. Here I have not been able to get any pick up group to loot this way...So I just go with what ever the group was doing.  <br>
  I was grouped with a monk in the geo's tunnle the other day.  A fine monk, and a great player.  After awhile I realized she should be starting to get overwieght.  I offered to exchange her change for my plat...and all of a sudden everyone acted as if i was trying to rob her!!!!   This struck me a very weird....everywhere else I have played the monks would often demand Autosplit be turned off, and would often not loot at all.   Here I have never seen a monk worry about weight here.<br>
  For this server most people seem to like Alpha looting, and or random looting.   Although they seem to like to random, they only seem to use the random to establish loot order.<br>
  As for the name calling...Your greedy...no you are greedy...wow! there is a lot of pot calling the kettle black here.  My point on greed is: what is wrong with greed?  It is the primary motivator in all players actions.  Seems it becomes a derogotory tag when some 'greedy' person runs some other 'greedy' person.<br>
<br>
Martty 44th Ranger of Tunare<br>
